```julia
function clean_column(col)
    return replace(lowercase(rstrip(col))), r"[ -]+" => "_")
end
```

This function first lowercases the column name `col`, then removes any leading or trailing whitespace using `rstrip`. The `replace` function is then used to replace any spaces and hyphens with an underscore. The regular expression `[ -]+` matches one or more space or hyphen characters.
